"11-50", "companyWebsite": "http://www.afs.org", "companyIndustry": "Non-profit Organizations", "logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4D0BAQFRGVpNoPb7Hg/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1719820616611/afs_intercultural_programs_logo?e=1775692800&v=beta&t=-tet9Giu9tVUd5EsR0-0s-I4Q8uqTlcVTC9Y3H-ahus", "title": "Sponsored Exchange Student", "jobDescription": null, "jobStartedOn": "8-2011", "jobEndedOn": "6-2012", "jobLocation": "Harwich, Massachusetts Area", "jobStillWorking": false, "jobLocationCountry": "US", "employmentType": null}], "updates": [{"postText": "\u2728 It\u2019s official \u2014 I\u2019m in the book \ud83d\udcd6\u2728\n\nWhen I first sat down for my interview with Izabela Duiwe, I didn\u2019t get the questions in advance \u2014 she wanted my story to be as authentic as possible. I came in unprepared, and what followed was an honest, flowing conversation that brought back so many hidden memories I hadn\u2019t realized were still with me.\n\nIn my chapter of The Women of Microsoft, I open up about the winding path I\u2019ve taken as both a pianist and a software engineer \u2014 two passions that may seem worlds apart, but together taught me discipline, creativity, and resilience. Along the way, I share practical strategies on balancing multiple roles, managing time effectively, and protecting energy to avoid burnout. These reflections were built over years of perseverance, growth, and self-discovery.\n\nThis book is more than a publication \u2014 it\u2019s a movement to celebrate the voices, journeys, and resilience of women in tech. Being part of this experience, alongside leaders whose journeys deeply inspired me, has been a real privilege. \n\nHuge thanks to Miri Rodriguez and Izabela Duiwe for bringing these stories to life! \ud83d\ude80 Launching today! Order your copy here: https://a.co/d/eH9Ky0Y and I am looking forward to hear what you think! #microsoft #microsoft50 #WomenInTech", "image": null, "postLink": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7363720090506194944?updateEntityUrn=urn%3Ali%3Afs_feedUpdate%3A%28V2%2Curn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7363720090506194944%29", "subTitle": null, "title": null, "type": "Post"}, {"postText": "Congrats team on winning not one, but two awards at Microsoft Hackathon!! I\u2019m truly grateful to have joined this project and worked with these amazing people. Excited to see what it will lead to next! \ud83c\udf89\ud83d\udc4f", "image": null, "postLink": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7123772518758318080?updateEntityUrn=urn%3Ali%3Afs_feedUpdate%3A%28V2%2Curn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7123772518758318080%29", "subTitle": null, "title": null, "type": "Post"}], "skills": [{"title": "Google Gemini"}, {"title": "MCP"}, {"title": "Model Context Protocol"}, {"title": "FastAPI"}, {"title": "Python"}, {"title": "AI Agent"}, {"title": "OpenAI API"}, {"title": "React.js"}, {"title": "Node.js"}, {"title": "Telegram Bot API"}, {"title": "Piano"}, {"title": "Data Analysis"}, {"title": "ABAP"}, {"title": "C#"}, {"title": "Microsoft Azure"}, {"title": "AEM"}, {"title": "Adobe Experience Manager (AEM)"}], "creatorWebsite": [], "profilePicAllDimensions": [], "educations": [{"companyId": "10802", "companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:10802", "companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/school/universityofbc/", "logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4E0BAQH415qlDBkj8Q/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1630608877834/universityofbc_logo?e=1775692800&v=beta&t=YOf-Dw8IxmpDPNkKljCQ9KDjx56kO8ahI3wbvrbb2l0", "title": "The University of British Columbia", "subtitle": "Bachelor of Science (B.Sc.), Combined Major in Computer Science and Statistics", "description": null, "grade": null, "period": {"startedOn": {"year": 2013, "month": 0}, "endedOn": {"year": 2017, "month": 0}}}, {"companyId": null, "companyUrn": null, "companyLink1": null, "logo": null, "title": "McMath Secondary School", "subtitle": null, "description": null, "grade": null, "period": {"sta